data.name: RTBChangeLog.Text
data.value:
Release 2.0.0
+ Added a utility tab to switch cold waters mods between the Dot mod and Vanilla +. Currently this is only available for me, but this is something that can be changed in future updates.
+ Added logging to tell us when Kyle’s server is active. There is no tab for it but it is something that is present.
+ Debugging has been altered to make future server additions easier to add. Such as with the auto syncs.
+ Code has been shifted to group it together in the main class.
- Code to add word wrap for the Log textbox has been removed after testing.
- Removed code for debugging issue #10.
Issue #35: UI Buttons: When performing a sync of a server, either upload or download, the user could still start the server, trigger a manual check or trigger another sync. As such, code has been amended to disable the buttons during a sync to prevent such an issue from occurring.
Issue #27: Dynamically Alter Show Server Pages: The sync menu will now show tabs and run code based on what is in your configuration file. If there is now Minecraft 1.7.10 server present, then you will not see a tab for it and the code for it will not run.
Issue #34: Exit Minecraft Server: Instead of waiting 10 seconds before closing the server, the program now looks for the last line outputted by the server. It then closes the server. The buttons also have been encapsulated in a try catch to prevent it crashing if there is an error at startup.
